{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17633341","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17633341"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:51:44+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:51:44+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17471"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17471","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17471"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10161"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70760"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10161","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10161"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17471"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56226"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5421"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23761"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23795"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70760","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70760"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDomestic violence is a significant public health issue that affects approximately one in four women and one in sixteen men in Australia.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes a key characteristic of domestic violence?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Most commonly affects women aged 18-45 years","Requires repeated episodes of abuse over time","Involves a pattern of coercive controlling behaviour","Usually begins with financial or social control","Typically escalates from verbal to physical abuse"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDomestic violence is characterised by a \u003Cstrong\u003Epattern of coercive controlling behaviour\u003C/strong\u003E. This can include physical, emotional, financial, social, and sexual abuse. The perpetrator uses these behaviours to maintain power and control over the victim.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cul\u003E                \u003Cli\u003EWhile domestic violence \u003Cstrong\u003Emost commonly affects women aged 18-45 years\u003C/strong\u003E, it occurs across all age groups and genders.\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003EWhile domestic violence often involves \u003Cstrong\u003Erepeated episodes of abuse over time\u003C/strong\u003E, even a single incident can constitute domestic violence.\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003EWhile domestic violence may \u003Cstrong\u003Eusually begin with financial or social control\u003C/strong\u003E, it can start with any form of abuse.\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003EWhile abuse may \u003Cstrong\u003Etypically escalate from verbal to physical abuse\u003C/strong\u003E, this pattern is not universal and some cases never involve physical violence.\u003C/li\u003E        \u003C/ul\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding that domestic violence is about power and control rather than just physical violence is crucial for healthcare providers to identify and respond appropriately to affected patients.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Domestic violence affects people of all socioeconomic backgrounds, ages, and cultural groups.","Physical abuse is only one form of domestic violence alongside emotional, financial, social, and sexual abuse.","Healthcare providers have a professional responsibility to screen for and respond appropriately to domestic violence."],"references":["Dheensa S, McLindon E, Spencer C, et al. Healthcare Professionals\u0027 Own Experiences of Domestic Violence and Abuse: A Meta-Analysis of Prevalence and Systematic Review of Risk Markers and Consequences. Trauma Violence Abuse. 2023;24(3):1282-1299. doi:10.1177/15248380211061771"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56226"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17471"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56226","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56226"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-16T13:48:28+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-04T00:07:53+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10161"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70760"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"5326","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5326"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf0f","name":"Public Health","synonyms":null,"description